<!-- ABOUT / OVERVIEW -->
<section class="section" id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="overview-grid">
      <div class="overview-text">
        <p class="section-label">Professional Overview</p>
        <h2 id="about-heading">London Barrister Focused on Costs Law</h2>
        <div class="section-rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <p>He was ranked in the Legal 500 2025 as having an "encyclopaedic knowledge of costs law" and appears for both receiving and paying parties at all levels of costs assessment, including seven-figure bills instructed unled.</p>
        <p>His insurance practice covers the full spectrum from complex policy wording disputes to straightforward property damage claims, regularly acting in cases worth over £500,000 for both Claimants and Defendants.</p>
        <div class="stat-row">
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-num">1,000+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Personal Injury Cases</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-num">£1M+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">High-Value Claims</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="overview-bio">
        <p>He has extensive knowledge of new and old fixed costs regimes and is a first-line resource for client queries when costs disputes arise. He typically handles claims in the £100,000 upward range, as well as those exceeding £1 million.</p>
        <p>He has worked on more than 1,000 personal injury cases across his career. His practice is managed by Lily Baker at 12 King's Bench Walk.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

